parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shimmy when braking, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shimmies or vibrates when braking
the steering wheel shakes
the brakes pulsate
and the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control or crash, especially when braking on slippery or uneven surfaces.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the vehicle experiences unwanted anti-lock activation
the brakes feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle bearings can cause unusual wear patterns, leading to premature wear of the axle, and potentially causing loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: Unusual noise from the rear end
loud noise from the rear end
premature wear of the axle bearings
loss of fluid in the rear end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tachometer can cause the engine to overspeed, potentially leading to engine damage and repair problems.
symptoms: Tachometer is reporting incorrectly
engine is overspeeding
potential repair problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The "Skip Shift" feature can prevent shifting from 1st to 2nd gear under certain circumstances, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Unable to shift into 2nd gear
loss of power
stuck in 1st gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stock shifter can cause mis-shifts, leading to loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Mis-shifts
loss of control
rear tires lose traction
engine over-revving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including dimming headlights, slow power windows, and reduced heating and air conditioning performance, which can lead to accidents or discomfort while driving.
symptoms: Headlights dim or flicker
power windows roll up and down slowly
heating and air conditioning performance is reduced
instrument panel does not illuminate
battery voltage gauge drops below normal levels
gauges reset or go haywire
trip odometer resets.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The alternator and battery voltage issues can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalls when coming to a stop
battery voltage gauge drops below 13
engine stalls after filling the vehicle with gas
battery voltage gauge drops below 8 volts.
